                  ISC-003D Inquiries and Incidents ITV Forum
                          Tuesday 06 November 2001
                                1000-1400 MST
                                1200-1600 EST

      Download Materials (documents will open in a separate window)
      ITV Goal and Objectives
      ITV Incident Notice redline version
      ITV Incident Order final version 2001
      ITV Incident Resolution Matrix

      DOE N 471-3 Reporting ISC (flow chart)
      Draft DOE O 471.XX (proposed mods) Flow Chart
      Draft DOE O 471.XX Flow Chart
      Incident-Inquiry Report (10-23-01)
      Inquiry Report Form Parts A-B (5-16-01)

      Prerequisites
      None

      Questions
      E-mail Jim L. Russell, Lead Instructor: jrussell@nnsi.doe.gov

      Target Audience

        * Managers and Staff responsible for incident reporting
        * All S&S Directors
        * All CMPC and FSA Quality Panel Members
        * All Chairpersons of other Quality Panels All Training Coordinators
        * All Security Representives for Program Offices

      What Content Will Be Covered
      The forum will be used to discuss lessons learned from the incident
      reporting process for inclusion into the draft Incident Reporting Order
      471.3.

      Who Are The Presenters
      Ray Holmer, DOE HQ; Dr. James Hickok, NNSI; Michael Schwartz, PNL; and
      Cindy Parnell, PNL

      References
      DOE N 471.3
      DOE M 471.2-1B, Chapter IV

      Preregister for this course:
      by COB November 2, 2001

      How to register
      To register for this training program, see your local site training
      point of contact or call Registration at (505) 845-5170, ext. 310 to
      identify your point of contact. [Washington/Germantown point of
      contact: Chuck Heubusch at (301) 903-5439.]

   If you intend to register for this course, please do so as soon as
   possible to allow for effective planning.

      Downlink information
      If you are a site facilitator with technical questions about the
      broadcast, contact Lori Davis at (505) 845-5170, ext. 322
      (Ldavis@nnsi.doe.gov).


